</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Settings Menu Requirement</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Notes</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV settings are either adjusted from the Settings menu on the TV using t=
he IR remote or from the SmartCast Mobile app.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV settings is known as the sidebar.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When SmartCast Mobile app is used to adjust the system settings, the ord=
er is the same as the Settings menu displayed on the TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Differences are only as required for settings as per limitation of the a=
pp.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When a system setting is changed using SmartCast Mobile app, a notificat=
ion displays confirming the change has been completed with exception that c=
hanges to most parental control settings do NOT display a notification on t=
he TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When SmartCast Mobile app is used to adjust the value of a slider, the a=
djustment is also annunciated on the TV with a slider (no notification in t=
his case). &nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When the MENU or gear key is first pressed, the header for the menu is S=
ettings.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The default selected setting is the top setting (Bluetooth Headphones) i=
f no selection previously made. Thereafter All Settings launches with the l=
ast used setting selected.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV Settings Timeout and Dismissal:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>For all skus, after the last key press timer starts. After 1 minute of s=
creen quiescence the sidebar is dismissed.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>During one 1 minute timer, if another key press the restart the 1 minute=
 timer.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Tuner Scan complete then 1 minute timer starts.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>For OLED sidebar timeout is after 1 minute of quiescence to prevent scre=
en burn.</p></li>
<li>
<p>A key press that displays another UI takes down the sidebar including:</=
p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>INPUT, PIC, MIC, WIDE, HOME, partner keys</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"rn7xw0zz68">PIC key dismisses Quick and deep links=
 to Picture mode.</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>A key press that does not take down sidebar (TV Settings or Quick)</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>no dismissal with VOLUME or MUTE keys</p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"yzx60bsyxb">INFO displays the input change control=
 which displays concurrently with sidebar (no overlap)</span></p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"oplfklgoox">CC notifications and closed captions d=
o not take down TV settings or Quick.</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>For System Info after 5 minutes timer then sidebar is dismissed.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"utn441numi">Sidebar timeout timer is paused if Tal=
k Back is voicing, restarts after Talk Back is quiet.</span></p></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1 minute timeout does not apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>During tuner scan.</p></li>
<li>
<p>System Info (system info timeout after 5 minutes).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Hidden menu</p></li>
<li>
<p>non-customer facing ODM/SOC menus including factory menus</p></li>
<li>
<p>Talk Back voicing</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If a setting, option or name exceeds the maximum of 15 characters for in=
put name or 24 characters for TV name or does not fit then add ellipses to =
indicate the name is incomplete.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"l06h9c843k">If Loki has not received values from D=
TV service the first time leave setting blank (not a 0).</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"kjf4uqm6k4">This applies to Quick menu an</span></=
p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-3.0SettingsMenu-3.1SettingsMenuOrder"><br>
3.1 Settings Menu Order</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"wide" data-local-id=3D"29a1=
d720-e935-47ea-a2a1-f13291aa0174" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col style=3D"width: 118.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 614.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 186.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Sub menu</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Definition</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Notes</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Bluetooth Headphones</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the Bluetooth Headphones settings.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>No timeout with tuner scan</p></li>
<li>
<p>No timeout with System Info.</p></li>
</ol></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Picture</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the picture settings.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Audio</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the audio settings.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Network</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures and tests the network connection for the TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV Channels</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the tuner and parental controls. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accessibility</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures closed captions, video description, talk back and zoom mode f=
or all models with SmartCast TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>System</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures menu language, time and timers, TV and input names, power mod=
e, CEC, system PIN, mobile devices, voice remote and for applicable skus, t=
he OLED panel. &nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Admin &amp; Privacy</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Supports administrative tasks including reboot TV, system information, c=
heck for updates and reset to defaults. &nbsp;Configures viewing data, DAI =
settings and store demo. Displays the VIZIO privacy policy. &nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User Manual</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>downloads and displays the user manual app.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
